itemDescription: Great-grandmother of Diana, Princess of Wales (1869-1958)

wikipedia_page.main: Rosalind Cecilia Caroline Hamilton, Duchess of Abercorn,  (26 February 1869 – 18 January 1958; née Lady Rosalind Bingham) was a British aristocrat and the Duchess of Abercorn by marriage. She was a great-grandmother of Diana, Princess of Wales.

response: *Rosalind Hamilton, Duchess of Abercorn (1869–1958), British aristocrat
* Rosalind Hamilton, Duchess of Abercorn (1869–1958), wife of the 3rd Duke

*Charles Gordon-Lennox, 5th Duke of Richmond (1791–1860). Diana, Princess of Wales (1961–1997) descended from him through his daughter Lady Cecilia Catherine Gordon-Lennox and her daughter Rosalind Hamilton, Duchess of Abercorn.
